article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 80, Longwood 54
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Jereal Scott shot 60 percent from the floor and scored 15 points to help Stephen F. Austin cruise past Longwood 80-54 on Monday night. The Lumberjacks (2-0) got ahead early, shooting 48 percent in the first half and leading 34-24 at halftime. They never trailed in the second period and led by as many as 27 points late in the game. Darius Gardner was perfect from the free-throw line, making 10 of 10. He finished with 13 points for the Lumberjacks. Antonio Bostic helped out with 11 points. David Robinson led the Lancers (0-2) with 11 points. Longwood shot just 37 percent from the floor.
